🌸 StudyFlow

A cute but powerful all-in-one study productivity web app — built with pure HTML, CSS, and Vanilla JavaScript.

StudyFlow helps students manage subjects, track progress, use a Pomodoro timer, and revise with interactive flashcards — all in one aesthetic, distraction-free dashboard.

✨ Features
📊 Dashboard

Live study stats (sessions, study minutes, accuracy)

Weekly study visualization

Achievement badges system

Real-time clock & greeting

📚 Subject Management

Add subjects with:

Priority levels (High / Medium / Low)

Deadlines

Notes

Progress tracking (0–100%)

Visual progress bars

Quick edit & delete options

⏱️ Pomodoro Timer

Focus, Short Break & Long Break modes

Animated circular progress ring

Sound effects (toggleable)

Session logging

Weekly hour tracking

Auto-switch between focus and break

Keyboard shortcuts support

🃏 Flashcards System

Create custom decks

Add unlimited flashcards

Flip animation

Shuffle deck

Accuracy tracking

Confetti on completion 🎉

📈 Progress Tracking

Weekly bar chart

Doughnut chart for accuracy (Chart.js)

Subject-wise progress

Achievement unlocking system

💾 Data Persistence

LocalStorage-based state management

Auto-save

Export data as JSON backup

Import previous data

Clear all data option

🎨 UI & UX

Dark / Light theme toggle

Kawaii-inspired UI

Toast notifications

Confetti animations

Sound effects using Web Audio API

Keyboard shortcuts for power users

🛠 Tech Stack

HTML5

CSS3

Vanilla JavaScript (ES6)

Chart.js (for progress visualization)

Web Audio API

LocalStorage API

🚀 How to Run

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/ipsyume/studyflow.git

Open index.html in your browser.

That’s it. No installation required.

          
